    <title>Available Constants</title>

    <para> When using Majisti_Application, a set of available constants are
        declared by default. These are the only trade off you get for using the
        framework, along with those of Zend. Anyhow, these constants are based
        on common standards, and will prove very usefull in any application. </para>
    <note>
        <para> Note that within Majisti, every paths do not contain the ending
            slash, this is to simplify path concatenation. </para>
    </note>

    <!-- List of constants -->
    <table>
        <title/>
        <tgroup cols="2">
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry>Constant</entry>
                    <entry>Description</entry>
                    <entry>Alias</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_ENVIRONNEMENT</entry>
                    <entry>The application environnement based on what was
                        setup in the application's htaccess. Usually
                        development, production testing, staging.</entry>
                    <entry>APP_ENV</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_LIBRARY</entry>
                    <entry>This is where the library folder resides in a
                        project Ex: /var/www/MyProject/library</entry>
                    <entry>APP_LIB</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_LOCALE_CURRENT</entry>
                    <entry>Application's current locale. Ex: en, fr, es,
                        etc.</entry>
                    <entry>APP_LANG</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_LOCALE_DEFAULT</entry>
                    <entry>Application's default local.</entry>
                    <entry>APP_LANG_DEF</entry>
                </row>

                <!-- APPLICATION_PATH -->
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_PATH</entry>
                    <entry>This is where the application folder resides inside a
                        project. This is an absolute path. Ex:
                        /var/www/MyProject/application</entry>
                    <entry>APP_PATH</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_URL</entry>
                    <entry>Simply BASE_URL appended to
                        APPLICATION_URL_PREFIX</entry>
                    <entry>APP_URL</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_URL_IMAGES</entry>
                    <entry>Application url to images files under public/images
                        directory</entry>
                    <entry>APP_IMAGES</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_URL_IMAGES_LOCALE</entry>
                    <entry>URL leading to the project's locale images folder.
                        Made of BASE_URL/images/current-locale</entry>
                    <entry>APP_IMG_LOC</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_URL_PREFIX</entry>
                    <entry>Composed of request scheme and http host. Ex:
                        http://localhost</entry>
                    <entry>No alias</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_URL_STYLES</entry>
                    <entry>Application url to stylesheets under styles
                        directory</entry>
                    <entry>APP_STYLES</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>APPLICATION_URL_SCRIPTS</entry>
                    <entry>Application url to javascript files under
                        public/scripts directory</entry>
                    <entry>APP_SCRIPTS</entry>
                </row>

                <!-- APPLICATION_LIBRARY -->
                
                <!-- APPLICATION_ENVIRONNEMENT -->
                
                <!-- BASE_URL -->
                <row>
                    <entry>BASE_URL</entry>
                    <entry>This is the base url of the application. This is an
                        alias to the http request
                            <methodname>Zend_Controller_Request_Http::getBaseUrl()</methodname>
                            function. Ex: /MyProject/public</entry>
                    <entry>No alias</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>JQUERY</entry>
                    <entry>Jquery's public directory URL. JQuery is located in
                        the library's public directory. Made of
                        MAJISTI_PUBLIC/jquery</entry>
                    <entry>JQ</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>JQUERY_PLUGINS</entry>
                    <entry>URL leading to JQuery plugins, wich are located in
                        majistix/jquery/plugins</entry>
                    <entry>JQ_PLUG</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>JQUERY_STYLES</entry>
                    <entry>URL leading to JQuery styles, wich are located in
                        majistix/jquery/styles</entry>
                    <entry>JQ_STYLES</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>JQUERY_THEMES</entry>
                    <entry>URL leading to JQuery themes, wich are located in
                        majistix/jquery/themes</entry>
                    <entry>JQ_THEMES</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>MAJISTI_PATH</entry>
                    <entry>/absolute/path/to/Majisti/library/Majisti</entry>
                    <entry>MAJ_PATH</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>MAJISTI_PUBLIC</entry>
                    <entry>This is really important since this is the public
                        access to the library. AJAX scripts, stylesheets or
                        images can be accessed directly with the autodetected
                        URL or by specifying a DNS. Commonly,
                        static.hostname.com is usually the DNS that points to
                        the public library. If not,
                        http://hostname:port/Majisti/public will be
                        used.</entry>
                    <entry>MAJ_PUB</entry>
                </row>

                <!-- MAJISTI_ROOT -->
                <row>
                    <entry>MAJISTI_ROOT</entry>
                    <entry>Majisti's root absolute path.
                        /absolute/path/to/Majisti/librar y</entry>
                    <entry>MAJ_ROOT</entry>
                </row>

